	<body>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+16" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">A modern wind turbine is a very large construction. The tower needs to rise at least 40 metres from the ground <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[1]</FONT> give the rotor blades enough clearance <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[2]</FONT> rotate safely. The blades are 20 metres from hub to tip. Their pitch can be altered <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[3]</FONT> they can catch the most wind. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph height="0" width="605" y="+16" x="12"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT SIZE="2"></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">At the top of the tower is the nacelle, <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[4]</FONT> streamlined <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[5]</FONT> to prevent the tower from bending in strong winds. Inside <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[6]</FONT> housing, the gearbox converts the 34 r.p.m. rotating speed of the rotor blades to 1500 r.p.m. <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[7]</FONT> the generator drive shaft. This is <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[8]</FONT> that the turbine produces electricity of the right frequency. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph height="0" width="605" y="+16" x="12"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT SIZE="2"></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">The turbine also has weather sensors, <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[9]</FONT> located at the top of the nacelle. These measure the speed and direction of the wind. This information is sent to the yaw drive, <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[10]</FONT> turns the turbine to face the wind. As a result, the turbine is always positioned to make the best use of the available wind.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
